('ACU-SKILL-1448', 'exploiting-broken-function-level-authorization', 'Exploiting Broken Function Level Authorization', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Tests APIs for Broken Function Level Authorization (BFLA) vulnerabilities where regular users can invoke administrative functions or access privileged API endpoints by directly calling them. The tester identifies admin and privileged endpoints, then attempts to access them with regular user credentials by manipulating HTTP methods, URL paths, and request parameters. Maps to OWASP API5:2023 Broken Function Level Authorization. Activates for requests involving BFLA testing, admin endpoint bypass, ', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "red-team", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1449', 'exploiting-broken-link-hijacking', 'Exploiting Broken Link Hijacking', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Discover and exploit broken link hijacking vulnerabilities by identifying references to expired domains, decommissioned cloud resources, and dead external services that can be claimed by an attacker.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1450', 'exploiting-constrained-delegation-abuse', 'Exploiting Constrained Delegation Abuse', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Exploit Kerberos Constrained Delegation misconfigurations in Active Directory to impersonate privileged users via S4U2self and S4U2proxy extensions for lateral movement and privilege escalation.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1451', 'exploiting-deeplink-vulnerabilities', 'Exploiting Deeplink Vulnerabilities', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Tests and exploits deep link (URL scheme and App Link) vulnerabilities in Android and iOS mobile applications to identify unauthorized access, data injection, intent hijacking, and redirect manipulation. Use when assessing mobile app attack surface through custom URI schemes, Android App Links, iOS Universal Links, or intent-based navigation. Activates for requests involving deep link security testing, URL scheme exploitation, mobile intent abuse, or link hijacking.
