', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1677', 'performing-graphql-depth-limit-attack', 'Performing Graphql Depth Limit Attack', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Execute and test GraphQL depth limit attacks using deeply nested recursive queries to identify denial-of-service vulnerabilities in GraphQL APIs.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1678', 'performing-graphql-introspection-attack', 'Performing Graphql Introspection Attack', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Performs GraphQL introspection attacks to extract the full API schema including types, queries, mutations, subscriptions, and field definitions from GraphQL endpoints. The tester uses introspection queries to map the attack surface, identifies sensitive fields and mutations, tests for query depth and complexity limits, and exploits GraphQL-specific vulnerabilities including batching attacks, alias-based brute force, and nested query DoS. Activates for requests involving GraphQL security testing,', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1679', 'performing-graphql-security-assessment', 'Performing Graphql Security Assessment', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Assessing GraphQL API endpoints for introspection leaks, injection attacks, authorization flaws, and denial-of-service vulnerabilities during authorized security tests.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1680', 'performing-hash-cracking-with-hashcat', 'Performing Hash Cracking With Hashcat', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Hash cracking is an essential skill for penetration testers and security auditors to evaluate password strength. Hashcat is the world''s fastest password recovery tool, supporting over 300 hash types w', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1681', 'performing-http-parameter-pollution-attack', 'Performing Http Parameter Pollution Attack', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Execute HTTP Parameter Pollution attacks to bypass input validation, WAF rules, and security controls by injecting duplicate parameters that are processed differently by front-end and back-end systems.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "red-team", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1682', 'performing-ics-asset-discovery-with-claroty', 'Performing Ics Asset Discovery With Claroty', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform comprehensive ICS/OT asset discovery using Claroty xDome platform, leveraging passive monitoring, Claroty Edge active queries, and integration ecosystem to gain full visibility into industrial control system assets including PLCs, RTUs, HMIs, and network infrastructure across Purdue Model levels.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1683', 'performing-initial-access-with-evilginx3', 'Performing Initial Access With Evilginx3', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform authorized initial access using EvilGinx3 adversary-in-the-middle phishing framework to capture session tokens and bypass multi-factor authentication during red team engagements.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "red-team", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1684', 'performing-insider-threat-investigation', 'Performing Insider Threat Investigation', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Investigates insider threat incidents involving employees, contractors, or trusted partners who misuse authorized access to steal data, sabotage systems, or violate security policies. Combines digital forensics, user behavior analytics, and HR/legal coordination to build an evidence-based case. Activates for requests involving insider threat investigation, employee data theft, privilege misuse, user behavior anomaly, or internal threat detection.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1685', 'performing-ioc-enrichment-automation', 'Performing Ioc Enrichment Automation', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Automates Indicator of Compromise (IOC) enrichment by orchestrating lookups across VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, Shodan, MISP, and other intelligence sources to provide contextual scoring and disposition recommendations. Use when SOC analysts need rapid multi-source enrichment of IPs, domains, URLs, and file hashes during alert triage or incident investigation.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1686', 'performing-iot-security-assessment', 'Performing Iot Security Assessment', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Performs comprehensive security assessments of IoT devices and their ecosystems by testing hardware interfaces, firmware, network communications, cloud APIs, and companion mobile applications. The tester uses firmware extraction and analysis, hardware debugging via UART and JTAG, network protocol analysis, and runtime exploitation to identify vulnerabilities across all layers of the IoT stack. Activates for requests involving IoT security testing, embedded device assessment, firmware security an', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1687', 'performing-ip-reputation-analysis-with-shodan', 'Performing Ip Reputation Analysis With Shodan', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Analyze IP address reputation using the Shodan API to identify open ports, running services, known vulnerabilities, and hosting context for threat intelligence enrichment and incident triage.', '{"thread": "T06 \u2014 EDNA", "thread_code": "T06", "category": "threat-intelligence", "shard_affinity": "Edna-SIGINT", "layer_access": ["L7", "L8", "L9"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'restricted', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1688', 'performing-jwt-none-algorithm-attack', 'Performing Jwt None Algorithm Attack', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Execute and test the JWT none algorithm attack to bypass signature verification by manipulating the alg header field in JSON Web Tokens.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "red-team", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1689', 'performing-kerberoasting-attack', 'Performing Kerberoasting Attack', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Kerberoasting is a post-exploitation technique that targets service accounts in Active Directory by requesting Kerberos TGS (Ticket Granting Service) tickets for accounts with Service Principal Names', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1690', 'performing-kubernetes-cis-benchmark-with-kube-bench', 'Performing Kubernetes Cis Benchmark With Kube Bench', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Audit Kubernetes cluster security posture against CIS benchmarks using kube-bench with automated checks for control plane, worker nodes, and RBAC.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1691', 'performing-kubernetes-etcd-security-assessment', 'Performing Kubernetes Etcd Security Assessment', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Assess the security posture of Kubernetes etcd clusters by evaluating encryption at rest, TLS configuration, access controls, backup encryption, and network isolation.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1692', 'performing-lateral-movement-detection', 'Performing Lateral Movement Detection', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Detects lateral movement techniques including Pass-the-Hash, PsExec, WMI execution, RDP pivoting, and SMB-based spreading using SIEM correlation of Windows event logs, network flow data, and endpoint telemetry mapped to MITRE ATT&CK Lateral Movement (TA0008) techniques.
', '{"thread": "T06 \u2014 EDNA", "thread_code": "T06", "category": "threat-intelligence", "shard_affinity": "Edna-SIGINT", "layer_access": ["L7", "L8", "L9"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'restricted', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1693', 'performing-lateral-movement-with-wmiexec', 'Performing Lateral Movement With Wmiexec', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform lateral movement across Windows networks using WMI-based remote execution techniques including Impacket wmiexec.py, CrackMapExec, and native WMI commands for stealthy post-exploitation during red team engagements.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1694', 'performing-linux-log-forensics-investigation', 'Performing Linux Log Forensics Investigation', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform forensic investigation of Linux system logs including syslog, auth.log, systemd journal, kern.log, and application logs to reconstruct user activity, detect unauthorized access, and establish event timelines on compromised Linux systems.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1695', 'performing-log-analysis-for-forensic-investigation', 'Performing Log Analysis For Forensic Investigation', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Collect, parse, and correlate system, application, and security logs to reconstruct events and establish timelines during forensic investigations.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1696', 'performing-log-source-onboarding-in-siem', 'Performing Log Source Onboarding In Siem', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform structured log source onboarding into SIEM platforms by configuring collectors, parsers, normalization, and validation for complete security visibility.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1697', 'performing-malware-hash-enrichment-with-virustotal', 'Performing Malware Hash Enrichment With Virustotal', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Enrich malware file hashes using the VirusTotal API to retrieve detection rates, behavioral analysis, YARA matches, and contextual threat intelligence for incident triage and IOC validation.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "malware", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1698', 'performing-malware-persistence-investigation', 'Performing Malware Persistence Investigation', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Systematically investigate all persistence mechanisms on Windows and Linux systems to identify how malware survives reboots and maintains access.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "malware", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1699', 'performing-malware-triage-with-yara', 'Performing Malware Triage With Yara', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Performs rapid malware triage and classification using YARA rules to match file patterns, strings, byte sequences, and structural characteristics against known malware families and suspicious indicators. Covers rule writing, scanning, and integration with analysis pipelines. Activates for requests involving YARA rule creation, malware classification, pattern matching, sample triage, or signature-based detection.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "malware", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1700', 'performing-memory-forensics-with-volatility3', 'Performing Memory Forensics With Volatility3', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Analyze volatile memory dumps using Volatility 3 to extract running processes, network connections, loaded modules, and evidence of malicious activity.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1701', 'performing-memory-forensics-with-volatility3-plugins', 'Performing Memory Forensics With Volatility3 Plugins', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Analyze memory dumps using Volatility3 plugins to detect injected code, rootkits, credential theft, and malware artifacts in Windows, Linux, and macOS memory images.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1702', 'performing-mobile-app-certificate-pinning-bypass', 'Performing Mobile App Certificate Pinning Bypass', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Bypasses SSL/TLS certificate pinning implementations in Android and iOS applications to enable traffic interception during authorized security assessments. Covers OkHttp, TrustManager, NSURLSession, and third-party pinning library bypass techniques using Frida, Objection, and custom scripts. Activates for requests involving certificate pinning bypass, SSL pinning defeat, mobile TLS interception, or proxy-resistant app testing.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "red-team", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1703', 'performing-mobile-device-forensics-with-cellebrite', 'Performing Mobile Device Forensics With Cellebrite', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Acquire and analyze mobile device data using Cellebrite UFED and open-source tools to extract communications, location data, and application artifacts.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1704', 'performing-network-forensics-with-wireshark', 'Performing Network Forensics With Wireshark', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Capture and analyze network traffic using Wireshark and tshark to reconstruct network events, extract artifacts, and identify malicious communications.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1705', 'performing-network-packet-capture-analysis', 'Performing Network Packet Capture Analysis', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform forensic analysis of network packet captures (PCAP/PCAPNG) using Wireshark, tshark, and tcpdump to reconstruct network communications, extract transferred files, identify malicious traffic, and establish evidence of data exfiltration or command-and-control activity.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1706', 'performing-network-traffic-analysis-with-zeek', 'Performing Network Traffic Analysis With Zeek', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Deploy Zeek network security monitor to capture, parse, and analyze network traffic metadata for threat detection, anomaly identification, and forensic investigation.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "forensics", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1707', 'performing-nist-csf-maturity-assessment', 'Performing Nist Csf Maturity Assessment', '1.0.0', 'security', 'The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0, released in February 2024, provides a comprehensive taxonomy for managing cybersecurity risk through six core Functions: Govern, Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover. This skill covers conducting a maturity assessment against the CSF, using the four Implementation Tiers (Partial, Risk-Informed, Repeatable, Adaptive) to measure organizational cybersecurity posture and create improvement roadmaps.', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1708', 'performing-oauth-scope-minimization-review', 'Performing Oauth Scope Minimization Review', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Performs OAuth 2.0 scope minimization review to identify over-permissioned third-party application integrations, excessive API scopes, unused token grants, and risky OAuth consent patterns across identity providers and SaaS platforms. Activates for requests involving OAuth scope audit, API permission review, third-party app risk assessment, or consent grant minimization.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1709', 'performing-oil-gas-cybersecurity-assessment', 'Performing Oil Gas Cybersecurity Assessment', '1.0.0', 'security', 'This skill covers conducting cybersecurity assessments specific to oil and gas facilities including upstream (exploration/production), midstream (pipeline/transport), and downstream (refining/distribution) operations. It addresses SCADA systems controlling pipeline operations, DCS for refinery process control, safety instrumented systems for hazardous processes, remote terminal units at unmanned wellhead sites, and compliance with API 1164, TSA Pipeline Security Directives, IEC 62443, and NIST C', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community')
;

INSERT INTO marketplace_skills (skill_id, name, display_name, version, domain, description, manifest, governance_level, psi_minimum, status, author) VALUES
('ACU-SKILL-1710', 'performing-open-source-intelligence-gathering', 'Performing Open Source Intelligence Gathering', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Open Source Intelligence (OSINT) gathering is the first active phase of a red team engagement, where operators collect publicly available information about the target organization to identify attack s', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1711', 'performing-ot-network-security-assessment', 'Performing Ot Network Security Assessment', '1.0.0', 'security', 'This skill covers conducting comprehensive security assessments of Operational Technology (OT) networks including SCADA systems, DCS architectures, and industrial control system communication paths. It addresses the Purdue Reference Model layers, identifies IT/OT convergence risks, evaluates firewall rules between zones, and maps industrial protocol traffic (Modbus, DNP3, OPC UA, EtherNet/IP) to detect misconfigurations, unauthorized connections, and attack surfaces in critical infrastructure.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "security", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1712', 'performing-ot-vulnerability-assessment-with-claroty', 'Performing Ot Vulnerability Assessment With Claroty', '1.0.0', 'security', 'This skill covers performing vulnerability assessments in OT environments using the Claroty xDome platform for comprehensive asset discovery, risk scoring, vulnerability correlation, and remediation prioritization. It addresses passive vulnerability identification through traffic analysis, active safe querying of OT devices, integration with CVE databases and ICS-CERT advisories, and risk-based prioritization that accounts for operational impact and compensating controls.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
('ACU-SKILL-1713', 'performing-ot-vulnerability-scanning-safely', 'Performing Ot Vulnerability Scanning Safely', '1.0.0', 'security', 'Perform vulnerability scanning in OT/ICS environments safely using passive monitoring, native protocol queries, and carefully controlled active scanning with Tenable OT Security to identify vulnerabilities without disrupting industrial processes or crashing legacy controllers.
', '{"thread": "T08 \u2014 ZURD", "thread_code": "T08", "category": "pentesting", "shard_affinity": "Tenebris-ACIWS", "layer_access": ["L8", "L9", "L10"], "source_repo": "mukul975/Anthropic-Cybersecurity-Skills"}', 'sovereign', 10.0, 'draft', 'cybersecurity-community'),
